         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Electric buses - cover purchase</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="34144910"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SUPPLIES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Procurement of up to 6 electric buses.</P>
               <P>The Contracting Authority uses Mercell Sourcing Service. To express your interest and gain access to any documents, please click on the link below or copy and paste the link into your browser:</P>
               <P>— https://permalink.mercell.com/78724308.aspx</P>
               <P>Follow the instructions listed on the webpage.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL CURRENCY="NOK">33000000.00</VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="NO032"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Cover purchase of 6 electric buses.</P>
                  <P>These must be compatible/communicate with Siemens charging stations in Drammen and Mjøndalen.</P>
                  <P>Due to problems with deliveries in the existing contract, Brakar intends to procure 4 to 6 electric buses as a cover purchase in order to operate bus route 51 that goes between Mjøndalen station in Nedre Eiker municipality and Drammen bus station. It is 15.2 km between the end stops on the route. Bus route 51 has a very flat profile with little ascents/descents. The height difference varies between 5 and 17 meters above sea level.</P>
                  <P>The buses shall be a 2-axle class 1 low floor or low entry and otherwise fulfill Brakar´s requirements for buses in the requirement specifications. A draft of the required specifications will be published shortly. The final requirement specifications will be sent out together with the invitation to confirm interest, see below.</P>
                  <P>All the buses in operation shall fulfill all the current laws and regulations and must be certified by the Norwegian Public Roads Administration.</P>
                  <P>The contract also includes maintenance and repair services for 6 years, with an option for 2+2 years, total 10 years.</P>
                  <P>Brakar has procured charging infrastructure from Siemens. The buses must be compatible with this charging infrastructure and the charging infrastructure shall be used in daily operations.</P>
                  <P>The specifications of the charging infrastructure will be in the requirement specification or will be published at a later date. A coordination contract will be signed between Brakar, Siemens and the bus supplier in order to facilitate this 3rd-party relationship in the best possible way.</P>
                  <P>It is advantageous if the buses are delivered quickly and the delivery time will, therefore, probably be an award criterium.</P>
                  <P>See the tender documentation.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
